Text.Value: All right, Karlach, all right. I'll leave it alone - for now.
This is the best day. The best day.

EditorData.NodeContext: Follow-up dialogue after Dammon fixed Karlach's engine so she can touch again

Text.Value: I'm not sure. Depends who's got me in mind.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC - Asked Karlach in her default branch

Text.Value: Thanks, soldier. Your support means I've got one less thing to worry about. That means a lot to me.
I'm so happy for you, Karlach.
I want to live too, but not under any circumstances. I have the power to choose, now. And I'm going to make that choice - myself.
Will you at least think about going back before it's too late?
Karlach, I'm worried about what Dammon said about your engine. We need to get you back to Avernus, or it's going to blow.
You're so stubborn. It's infuriating.
I'm so happy for you. For both of us, if I'm honest.
And for the first time in a decade, there are people I care about all around me. Let me enjoy that. Please.

EditorData.NodeContext: As in, 'drop the dark subject of my death. just let me enjoy this.'

Text.Value: I don't expect anyone to understand that. But I've been dealt a hand most people don't have to contemplate playing.
But - I don't want to talk about this now. I've been given a huge gift - I can touch the people I love for the first time in a decade.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated. Angry cause the player's making her face the possibility of dying when she's trying to enjoy being able to touch.

Text.Value: Look, I don't want to fight. That's the exact opposite of what I want to do right now. Let's start over. Hi, I'm Karlach, and I get to touch you any time I want. How about that?

EditorData.NodeContext: After fighting with the player (romance path), Karlach is bringing it back home - let's not do this. Let's just be happy I can finally touch again.

Text.Value: Not always. Not this. I'm sorry - but this one is mine.

Thank you, I try.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dry and stern. Not happy. But soon she'll try to make up.

Text.Value: Me too. Whenever you want to turn in, I'd love to take this whole touch thing for a test drive.

EditorData.NodeContext: Flirty but with a dash of bashfulness/ awkwardness.

Text.Value: Leave.
Nope! Thanks so much for asking though.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcastically ending the convo with the player after they won't drop the subject of her death, despite her asking that they do. She's being a brat here, with an edge of 'fuck off dude' to the player.

Text.Value: We're a team. We make these kinds of decisions together.
I know we have important things to do - but we deserve a little sweetness too.

I respect your decision.
You heard Dammon. There is no solution. It's Hell or bust. I choose bust.

EditorData.NodeContext: Being defiant toward the player who wants her to return to Avernus.

Text.Value: But I want you to live.
